.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-STATS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.52" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-stats \- Show tracked runtime metrics and step stats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose stats [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read tracked metrics and Slurm step statistics for a submitted job. Prefer machine\-readable formats when integrating with dashboards or experiment tooling.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to inspect instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--sweep\fR \fIID\fR
Aggregate per\-trial stats over all trials of this sweep id instead of a single job.
.TP
\fB--remote\fR \fIHOST\fR
Run this command on the login node's staged checkout from a prior `up \-\-remote`, over SSH, streaming output back. With no value, uses the configured login_host; accepts user@host (otherwise HPC_COMPOSE_REMOTE_USER / login_user / ~/.ssh/config).
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json, csv, jsonl.
.TP
\fB--accounting\fR
Include on\-demand sacct accounting rollups for completed or visible Slurm jobs.
.TP
\fB--sstat\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sstat executable. Default: sstat.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose stats \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose stats \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
hpc\-compose stats \-f compose.yaml \-\-format csv
.fi
